Definition: from {{h5937}}; exultant; that rejoiceth.
feminine from an unused root meaning to cover; dusk; dark, twilight.
feminine passive participle of an unused root meaning to suck; the leech; horse-leech.
a primitive root; to jump for joy, i.e. exult; be joyful, rejoice, triumph.
passive participle of {{h5956}} in the denominative sense of {{h5958}}; (only in plural as abstract) adolescence; figuratively, vigor; youth.
or עַלְיָן; from {{h5927}}; lofty; Alvan or Aljan, an Idumaean; Alian, Alvan.
for {{h5766}}; moral perverseness; iniquity.
or עַליָה; the same as {{h5932}}; Alvah or Aljah, an Idumaean; Aliah, Alvah.

or עוֹלָה; feminine active participle of {{h5927}}; a step or (collectively, stairs, as ascending); usually a holocaust (as going up in smoke); ascent, burnt offering (sacrifice), go up to. See also {{h5766}}.
(Aramaic) feminine from a root corresponding to {{h5927}}; a pretext (as arising artificially); occasion.
probably from the same as {{h5908}} in the secondary sense of attacking; a mouse (as nibbling); mouse.
probably from an unused root in the literal sense of entangling; a spider (as weaving a network); spider.
or עֵרֹם; from {{h6191}}; nudity; naked(-ness).
from {{h5892}}; city-wise; Iram, an Idumaean; Iram.
from {{h5892}}; urbane; Iri, an Israelite; Iri.
probably for {{h5909}}; Akbor, the name of an Idumaean and of two Israelites; Achbor.
or עָשׁ; from {{h5789}}; the constellation of the Great Bear (perhaps from its migration through the heavens); Arcturus.
from {{h5892}} and {{h8121}}; city of the sun; Ir-Shemesh, a place in Palestine; Irshemesh.
from {{h5892}} and {{h5175}}; city of a serpent; Ir-Nachash, a place in Palestine; Irnahash.
from {{h5971}}; tribal, i.e. inbred; Ammon, a son of Lot; also his posterity and their country; Ammon, Ammonites.
or עַמֻּד; from {{h5975}}; a column (as standing); also a stand, i.e. platform; × apiece, pillar.
the same as {{h5980}}; association; Ummah, a place in Palestine; Ummah.
from {{h6004}}; conjunction, i.e. society; mostly adverb or preposition (with prepositional prefix), near, beside, along with; (over) against, at, beside, hard by, in points.
from {{h6009}}; deep; Amok, an Israelite; Amok.
from {{h6006}}; burdensome; Amos, an Israelite prophet; Amos.
feminine of {{h5984}}; an Ammonitess; Ammonite(-ss).
patronymically from {{h5983}}; an Ammonite or (the adjective) Ammonitish; Ammonite(-s).
from {{h5971}} and {{h1935}}; people of splendor; Ammihud, the name of three Israelites; Ammihud.
from {{h5971}} and {{h410}}; people of God; Ammiel, the name of three or four Israelites; Ammiel.
a primitive root; to toil, i.e. work severely and with irksomeness; (take) labour (in).

from {{h5998}}; toil, i.e. wearing effort; hence, worry, whether of body or mind; grievance(-vousness), iniquity, labour, mischief, miserable(-sery), pain(-ful), perverseness, sorrow, toil, travail, trouble, wearisome, wickedness.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h6012}}; profound, i.e. unsearchable; deep.
from {{h6014}}; a bunch of grain; handful, sheaf.
from {{h5971}} and {{h7706}}; people of (the) Almighty; Ammishaddai, an Israelite; Ammishaddai.
from a primitive root meaning to associate; companionship; hence (concretely) a comrade or kindred man; another, fellow, neighbour.
from {{h5971}} and {{h2064}}; people of endowment; Ammizabad, an Israelite; Ammizabad.
from {{h5971}} and {{h2353}}; people of nobility; Ammichur, a Syrian prince; Ammihud (from the margin).
from {{h5971}} and {{h5068}}; people of liberality; Amminadab, the name of four Israelites; Amminadab.
from {{h5971}} and {{h5081}}; my people (is) liberal; Ammi-Nadib, probably an Israelite; Amminadib.
the same as {{h5999}}; Amal, an Israelite; Amal.
from {{h5913}}; a fetter; hence, an anklet; stocks, tinkling ornament.
feminine of {{h5914}}; anklet; Aksah, an Israelitess; Achsah.
a primitive root; properly, to roil water; figuratively, to disturb or affict; trouble, stir.
from {{h5916}}; troublesome; Akar, an Israelite; Achar. Compare {{h5912}}.
apparently from an unused root meaning to hem in; Akko (from its situation on a bay); Accho.
from {{h5916}}; troubled; Akor, the name of a place in Palestine; Achor.
from an unused root meaning to trouble; troublesome; Akan, an Israelite; Achan. Compare {{h5917}}.
a primitive root; properly, to tie, specifically, with fetters; but used only as denominative from {{h5914}}; to put on anklets; make a tinkling ornament.
from {{h5916}}; muddler; Okran, an Israelite; Ocran.
probably from an unused root meaning to coil; an asp (from lurking coiled up); adder.
plural of {{h5959}}; properly, girls, i.e. the soprano or female voice, perhaps falsetto; Alamoth.
from {{h5956}}; hidden; See also {{h5963}}.; Almon, a place in Palestine
from the same as {{h5960}} and the dual of {{h1960}} (compare {{h1015}}) with enclitic of direction; Almon towards Diblathajim; Almon-Diblathajemah, a place in Moab; Almondilathaim.
(Aramaic) patrial from a name corresponding to {{h5867}} contracted; an Elamite or inhabitant of Elam; Elamite.
a primitive root; to leap for joy, i.e. exult, wave joyously; × peacock, rejoice, solace self.
from {{h5956}}; a covering; Alemeth, the name of a place in Palestine and of two Israelites; Alameth, Alemeth.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h6763}}; a rib; rib.
a primitive root; to sip up; suck up.
from {{h5968}}; an envelope, i.e. (figuratively) mourning; fainted.
a primitive root; to veil or cover; figuratively, to be languid; faint, overlaid, wrap self.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5971}}; people.

from {{h6004}}; adverb or preposition, with (i.e. in conjunction with), in varied applications; specifically, equally with; often with prepositional prefix (and then usually unrepresented in English); accompanying, against, and, as (× long as), before, beside, by (reason of), for all, from (among, between), in, like, more than, of, (un-) to, with(-al).
a primitive root; to jump for joy, i.e. exult; be joyful, rejoice, triumph.
from {{h6004}}; a people (as a congregated unit); specifically, a tribe (as those of Israel); hence (collectively) troops or attendants; figuratively, a flock; folk, men, nation, people.
for {{h4571}}; to shake; be at a stand.
from {{h5975}}; a spot (as being fixed); place, (  where) stood, upright.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5973}}; by, from, like, to(-ward), with.

a primitive root; to stand, in various relations (literal and figurative, intransitive and transitive); abide (behind), appoint, arise, cease, confirm, continue, dwell, be employed, endure, establish, leave, make, ordain, be (over), place, (be) present (self), raise up, remain, repair,   serve, set (forth, over, -tle, up), (make to, make to be at a, with-) stand (by, fast, firm, still, up), (be at a) stay (up), tarry.
prolonged for {{h5973}}; along with; against, by, from, + me, + mine, of, + that I take, unto, upon, with(-in.)
from {{h5975}}; a station, i.e. domicile; standing.

or עֲלִלָה; from {{h5953}} in the sense of effecting; an exploit (of God), or a performance (of man, often in a bad sense); by implication, an opportunity; act(-ion), deed, doing, invention, occasion, work.
from {{h5953}} in the sense of completing; probably a crucible (as working over the metal); furnace.
from {{h5937}}; exultant; joyous, (that) rejoice(-ing)
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5945}}; the Supreme; Most high.
from {{h5927}}; an elevation, i.e. (adj.) lofty (compar.); as title, the Supreme; (Most, on) high(-er, -est), upper(-most).
feminine from {{h5927}}; something lofty, i.e. a stair-way; also a second-story room (or even one on the roof); figuratively, the sky; ascent, (upper) chamber, going up, loft, parlour.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5942}}; supreme (i.e. God); (most) high.
from {{h5927}}; high; i.e. comparative; upper.
from {{h5927}}; lofty; Eli, an Israelite highpriest; Eli.
from {{h5927}}; a pestle (as lifted); pestle.
from {{h5927}}; a leaf (as coming up on a tree); collectively, foliage; branch, leaf.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5930}}; a holocaust; burnt offering.
feminine of {{h5923}}; burden; Ulla, an Israelite; Ulla.
(Aramaic) from {{h5922}}; above; over.

a primitive root; to ascend, intransitively (be high) or actively (mount); used in a great variety of senses, primary and secondary, literal and figurative; arise (up), (cause to) ascend up, at once, break (the day) (up), bring (up), (cause to) burn, carry up, cast up,   shew, climb (up), (cause to, make to) come (up), cut off, dawn, depart, exalt, excel, fall, fetch up, get up, (make to) go (away, up); grow (over) increase, lay, leap, levy, lift (self) up, light, (make) up, × mention, mount up, offer, make to pay,   perfect, prefer, put (on), raise, recover, restore, (make to) rise (up), scale, set (up), shoot forth (up), (begin to) spring (up), stir up, take away (up), work.
from an unused root meaning to stutter; stuttering; stammerer.

properly, the same as {{h5920}} used as a preposition (in the singular or plural often with prefix, or as conjunction with a particle following); above, over, upon, or against (yet always in this last relation with a downward aspect) in a great variety of applications; above, according to(-ly), after, (as) against, among, and, × as, at, because of, beside (the rest of), between, beyond the time, × both and, by (reason of), × had the charge of, concerning for, in (that), (forth, out) of, (from) (off), (up-) on, over, than, through(-out), to, touching, × with.
from {{h5927}}; properly, the top; specifically, the Highest (i.e. God); also (adverb) aloft, to Jehovah; above, high, most High.
or עוֹל; from {{h5953}}; a yoke (as imposed on the neck), literally or figuratively; yoke.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5921}}; about, against, concerning, for, (there-) fore, from, in, × more, of, (there-, up-) on, (in-) to,   why with.
from {{h5956}}; (compare {{h5959}}); properly, something kept out of sight, i.e. a lad; young man, stripling.
feminine of {{h5958}}; a lass (as veiled or private); damsel, maid, virgin.
for {{h5949}}; (miraculous) execution; work.
from {{h5970}}; exultation; rejoicing.
from {{h5927}}; a second-story room; chamber. Compare {{h5944}}.

a primitive root; to effect thoroughly; specifically, to glean (also figuratively); by implication (in a bad sense) to overdo, i.e. maltreat, be saucy to, pain, impose (also literal); abuse, affect, × child, defile, do, glean, mock, practise, thoroughly, work (wonderfully).
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5953}} (in the sense of thrusting oneself in),; to enter; causatively, to introduce; bring in, come in, go in.
feminine active participle of {{h5953}}; only in plural gleanings; by extension gleaning-time; (gleaning) (of the) grapes, grapegleanings.
a primitive root; to veil from sight, i.e. conceal (literally or figuratively); × any ways, blind, dissembler, hide (self), secret (thing).
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5769}}; remote time, i.e. the future or past indefinitely; often adverb, forever; for (n-)ever (lasting), old.
